## Polyedro Labs UI System

All product UI in `apps/web` follows the **neobrutalist** design language. Do not introduce generic SaaS styling such as soft shadows, rounded-xl cards, zinc/emerald palettes, or gradients.

### Source of truth

| Layer                      | File                                                                  |
| -------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Design tokens              | `apps/web/src/components/labs/defs.ts`                                |
| CSS utilities & animations | `apps/web/src/index.css`                                              |
| Fonts (layout)             | `apps/web/src/app/layout.tsx` — Archivo, Archivo Black, IBM Plex Mono |

Always import tokens from `@/components/labs/defs`. Never hard-code hex values that already exist as constants.

### Color palette

**Ground** — structural layer

```txt
PAPER  #F4F2EC  — page background, input fills
INK    #0A0A0A  — text, borders, shadows
CARD   #FFFFFF  — card surfaces
STONE  #EDEAE0  — draft / idle states
```

**Signals** — semantic layer

```txt
ACID  #C6F432  — primary accent, CTAs, approved
VOLT  #2F5CE5  — agents, Push-to-Meta (use `textOnSignal(VOLT)` → white text)
CYAN  #45D8E8  — generating / in-progress
CORAL #FF6B57  — regen / errors
SUN   #FFD02F  — review / warnings
```

High contrast only. **No gradients** except the grid overlay from `gridBg()`.

### Typography

| Role           | Token        | Usage                                            |
| -------------- | ------------ | ------------------------------------------------ |
| Body           | `FONT_SANS`  | Paragraphs, inputs, buttons                      |
| Headlines      | `FONT_BLACK` | H1–H3, brand name "POLYEDRO"                     |
| Labels / specs | `FONT_MONO`  | Tags, status chips, step labels, version strings |

Use `monoLabel` preset for uppercase field labels (`fontSize: 10`, `letterSpacing: "0.1em"`).

Headlines: `letterSpacing: "-0.02em"` to `"-0.03em"`, tight line-height around `1.02–1.1`.

### Layout & surfaces

* Wrap product screens in `<div className="lab-root" style={{ minHeight: "100vh", background: PAPER, color: INK, fontFamily: FONT_SANS }}>`.
* Subtle grid: `backgroundImage: gridBg(0.035)` for main screens or `gridBg(0.045)` for onboarding/landing.
* Cards: spread `cardShell` — white background, `3px solid INK` border, hard offset shadow with `5px 5px 0 INK`.
* **Border radius is always 0** in product UI. No `rounded-*` on labs screens.
* Borders: `2px` for chips/toggles, `3px` for cards, inputs, and primary buttons.

### Interactive elements

```tsx
// Primary button — always pair nb-press with inline styles
<button
  className="nb-press"
  style={{
    fontFamily: FONT_SANS,
    fontWeight: 800,
    textTransform: "uppercase",
    background: ACID,
    border: `3px solid ${INK}`,
    padding: 16,
    cursor: "pointer",
  }}
>
  ACTION →
</button>

// Toggle / chip hover
<button className="hov-accent" style={{ border: `2px solid ${INK}`, ... }} />

// Links styled as buttons
<Link href="/" className="nb-press" style={{ ... }} />
```

CSS classes from `index.css`:

* `nb-press` — hard shadow that compresses on hover/active using `--sx`, `--sc` vars.
* `hov-accent` / `hov-sun` / `hov-paper` — flat hover fill swaps.
* Focus inside `.lab-root`: `outline: 3px solid INK`, no ring-offset.

### Brand wordmark

```tsx
<span style={{ fontFamily: FONT_BLACK, fontSize: 20, letterSpacing: "-0.02em" }}>POLYEDRO</span>
<span style={{ fontFamily: FONT_MONO, fontWeight: 700, background: ACID, padding: "0 5px", border: `2px solid ${INK}`, marginLeft: 6 }}>/abs</span>
```

Subtitle: `fontFamily: FONT_MONO`, `fontSize: 10`, `letterSpacing: "0.1em"`, muted `rgba(10,10,10,0.5)`.

### Voice UI Styling

When building ElevenLabs voice interfaces inside product screens:

* Use the same neobrutalist system.
* Voice states should map to existing signal colors:

  * idle/disconnected → `STONE`
  * connecting/generating → `CYAN`
  * listening/active → `VOLT`
  * speaking/ready → `ACID`
  * warning/permission needed → `SUN`
  * error/failed → `CORAL`
* Do not introduce glossy microphone widgets, blurred SaaS cards, or generic voice assistant gradients.
* Voice controls must be obvious, high contrast, and accessible.
* Always include a clear stop/end button for live sessions.
* Show microphone permission and recording/listening states visibly.

### Status & agent colors

| Status     | Background | Notes                                           |
| ---------- | ---------- | ----------------------------------------------- |
| draft      | STONE      | static                                          |
| generating | CYAN       | `animation: "pv-pulse 1s ease-in-out infinite"` |
| review     | SUN        | static                                          |
| approved   | ACID       | append " ✓" in label                            |

Agent glyph colors: see `AGENT_DEFS` / `RUN_DEFS` in `defs.ts`.

### Animations (`index.css`)

Use existing keyframes only:

* `pv-bar`
* `pv-pulse`
* `pv-rise`
* `pv-blink`
* `pv-spin`
* `pv-spin0`

### Dual styling zones

| Zone                                                 | Stack                                                     | When                                               |
| ---------------------------------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------- |
| **Product UI** (labs, landing, campaigns, voice UI)  | `defs.ts` tokens + inline `style` + `index.css` utilities | Default for all user-facing screens                |
| **Infrastructure** (providers, toasts, theme toggle) | `@Polyedro-abs/ui` shadcn + Tailwind                      | Shell utilities only — do not leak into labs views |

When building new screens, such as `/landing`, match existing labs components — not shadcn defaults.

Use Tailwind CSS, Shadcn UI, and Radix UI **only** in the infrastructure zone. Product screens always use the neobrutalist system above.

### UI Do / Don't

```txt
✅ Import ACID, INK, PAPER, CARD, cardShell, gridBg, monoLabel from defs.ts
✅ Hard shadows: boxShadow: `Npx Npx 0 ${INK}`
✅ Uppercase mono labels for form fields and tags
✅ White (CARD) card surfaces on PAPER background
✅ Consistent design and responsive patterns across platforms
✅ Voice UI states mapped to existing signal colors
✅ Clear microphone, listening, speaking, and error states

❌ rounded-lg / rounded-xl on product screens
❌ box-shadow with blur (e.g. shadow-md)
❌ Tailwind color classes (zinc-*, emerald-*) in labs/landing components
❌ New color tokens without adding them to defs.ts first
❌ DAIEGO UI (Poppins/zinc/emerald) — different product family
❌ Exposed ElevenLabs API keys in client components
❌ Hidden audio recording or unclear microphone state
```
